snippet.textDisplay:
The Chinese New Year is a joyous celebration of life renewed and hope for the coming new year. People who practice Falun Dafa, as well as those who do not, sent their sincere greetings to Mr. Li Hongzhi (the founder of Falun Dafa). The greetings came from China and at least 55 other countries and regions. People of all ages and from all walks of life expressed their sincere gratitude and say they see hope for the future in Falun Dafa.

Practitioners Feel Blessed
One greeting came from a family of four generations in Yantai City, Shandong Province. The lady said her mother suffered from rheumatoid arthritis. “Some of her joints were deformed. We tried everything, but nothing helped,” she wrote. “By practicing Falun Dafa, all her joints returned to normal and she can now walk with her back straight.” Others in the village were amazed and thought it was miraculous.

The lady’s 93-year-old grandmother's health also improved significantly after she began to practice. She no longer needs medication. She regained her eyesight and hearing, and most people think she's in her 70s. “Grandmother had cataracts. One day, she expelled a lot of phlegm and afterward her vision was fine,” she recalled.

The woman’s husband also experienced positive changes. Because of his incurable heart disease, he couldn't work. After he started to practice Falun Dafa, however, his heart disease went away and he changed dramatically, both physically and spiritually. “Instead of complaining or being cynical, my husband is now considerate and always willing to help. Looking at my husband—who is now healthy, positive, and open-minded—I know all these positive things happened because of Falun Dafa. Thank you, Master, for giving us a new life and a happy family!”

A practitioner in Daqing City, Heilongjiang Province, said that, when his grandson was born on October 2, 2019, he was diagnosed with cerebral palsy and put in intensive care. “With Master’s help, the boy improved. He was released from the hospital in eight days and was just fine.”
